('477210083', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Amazing app but...', 'I love Spotify it\'s a very well made and managed app but there are some changes that could be set in motion that would improve this app ten fold. \n1) Spotify needs to catch up and play at the speed of its competitors. A lot of times when a song drops on the radio, or a hit artist sets out their newest  album, it seems Spotify is the last to know. I believe that if I\'m paying $12 a month that I should get the whole shebang, I shouldn\'t have to gravitate towards YouTube because you guys don\'t move expeditiously, as you should for the owners of a multi million dollar app. YouTube moves faster than you and it\'s a primarily video streaming app, not a music app.\n2) The color theme. Personally I totally love your color theme because I don\'t have eye problems, but a lot of your subscribers do. I\'ve heard many complaints about how the white on black puts a strain on their eyes and gives them headaches. You guys should have a setting in which people can change the color and then of YOUR OWN account. (I.e. Gray, white, red, purple, whatever you\'d like) especially if your the one paying for it.\n           That\'s pretty much it for me I already fell in love with you guys, Spotify is life. Xoxo', '541980589', 'applestore', 'Mexico', 'Excellent App', 'The truth if it is worth downloading is very useful, works much better by contracting a premium plan as there are no ads or interruptions, you can download music and listen to it without the need to be connected to a network', 'Spotify', 0.138053, 1, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'all', 239, 2, 2, 1, 'ot', 'ot'),
