('87625119', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Dangerous to navigate app while driving!!', 'It\'s generally very good, but there are WAY too many clicks to navigate while you\'re driving, which, after all, is the point of the app. It\'s dangerous. \nI put in my destination before I start, but if I have to re-route for some reason, it\'s horrible. You have to go too deep into the settings to avoid toll roads, for example. \nThat should be a one-click. \nI have to fight with the app because it\'s always wants me to take the toll roads. Where I live, they usually only save me 3-5 minutes. Paying over $10 to save a few minutes is nuts, but the app will re-route me to onto the toll road if a call disrupts the navigation, the app closes itself, if I have to turn the app off for some reason, etc.\n\nI\'ve been using Waze for over five years. \nThe toll road thing drives me crazy!! It\'s been hazardous at times. \n\nMy other beef has been mentioned by several others - it\'s not easy to report a hazard, police, traffic, etc.\nThe icons should be bigger and therefore easier to click while driving. \n\nIt needs to be easier to tell which side my destination is on. Knowing whether to be on the right or left side much earlier would be a lot safer. \n\nAnother issue which should be addressed is the tardiness of the audio directions to turn. \nWhen the app says, \"Turn here,\" you\'re on top of the turn. There is absolutely no time to adjust if you weren\'t sure which turn it was. Sometimes they are close together and you\'re not sure till the last second. \nPLEASE adjust the timing on the verbal cue!!!\n\nOn the plus side, the navigation is usually pretty good to excellent. \nThe police reports from fellow drivers is a HUGE plus!!! \n\nPlease address these issues, Waze, and I\'ll change my rating. Thank you!!', '148801274', 'applestore', 'Mexico', 'Very good', 'Excellent tool for traffic, it would be nice to add the option of being able to put an event in a location that is within a radius close to me and that is not my position, since sometimes it is not possible to put it right at the moment', 'Waze', 0.26181, 0, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'all', 338, 0, 2, 0.75, 'ot', 'fr'),
