('191729621', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Was better before and a suggestion', 'I have been using Waze for a little over a year I think. With this new update it seems to be stuck on the same traffic. (Ground hog day!) every time I ask for traffic routes it says the exact same thing as the previous day. I know it\'s not accurate because a family member lives next door, we work at the same place and she has completely different route times than what mine says. I deleted and reinstalled twice, waiting 30 minutes just in case, but no change. \n\nMy Suggestion: it would be nice to have the option of seeing both freeways and side streets if one or the other is fastest/second fastest without having to turn on/off avoid highways button.', '293634656', 'applestore', 'Mexico', 'Excellent', 'Excellent application. Better every time.', 'Waze', 0.0766574, 0, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'long', 399, 0, 3, 0.625, 'ot', 'br'),
('193128578', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Great when it works', 'I would give it 5 stars because when it works it\'s great. But there are a lot of times, while driving somewhere I don\'t know at all (usually a long road trip) it will lose connection with the server. I\'ve had it happen for an hour where I\'m just driving blindly hoping the directions are stills accurate for time, completely unable to check routes. The only way to get it to connect again is to shut it off and restart hoping it will connect again that I won\'t be totally lost. But when it works, I find the time estimate is almost always accurate to the minute. Although sometimes it does send you on a weird route for no reason.', '317985846', 'applestore', 'Mexico', 'Excellent application', 'I was in France and Spain and it worked great', 'Waze', 0.0650571, 0, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'long', 400, 1, 3, 0.75, 'br', 'ot'),
('194074546', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Pretty good occasional weird muting', 'I don\'t have premium so my only complaint is that I miss features I have on the computer version when I\'m using the mobile version. That\'s more thanks to me being broke and less a part of the app itself. It hasn\'t crashed really, although it has randomly muted itself before and I\'m not sure why.', '198641119', 'applestore', 'Mexico', 'Equalizer Quality', 'I would like you to check the equalizer so that it can be modified during playback without having to exit the setup menu every time you want to change it. The sound does not have the quality that Deezer has. Could you please improve your app? Oh and also include an equalizer that can better adjust the sound quality? Maybe a parametric equalizer.', 'Spotify', 0.090021, 0, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'long', 401, 1, 0, 0.875, 'ot', 'ot'),
