('31189731', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Allow option to only use location when app is in use.', 'I understand that much of the data is collected from all users that have the app installed. However, by constantly using the users location, even when they are not using the app, you are draining the battery on a users phone tremendously. I have a brand new iPhone 7+ and this app will use 60% of my battery during an 8 hour shift at work. \n\nThere should be an option to only use data when the app is active. Right now I have to manually turn this ability on and off in my settings. \n\nGreat concept but the battery usage is makes the app useless unless you always have your phone plugged in.', '149342248', 'applestore', 'Mexico', 'An option for the driver', 'It is an app that offers many advantages when driving in a city as complicated as Mexico City. However it has areas of opportunity in the update when taking the best route.', 'Waze', 0.204088, 0, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'long', 492, 0, 0, 1, 'ot', 'fr'),
