('35450813', 'applestore', 'United States', 'Not as solid as before', 'I do very much like this app and use it to help manage traffic but its accuracy seems to have weakened a fair amount since I first got it. Whereas it used to do a great job of estimating my arrival time I now almost always arrive a fair amount later than it originally projected. I don\'t expect it to be a crystal ball but wonder if its popularity is hurting it as more follow its route advice. \n\nIt also seems like traffic jam data is more frequently faulty—I\'ll find myself in traffic that the app didn\'t know about or I\'ll be cruising along in an area that supposedly is jammed.\n\nIt may not be realistic, but I wish there were a way the app could direct you to the best side of a multi-lane road to minimize congestion around an accident or intersection. \n\nThat said, I still really appreciate the unconventional alternates offered and navigation help this app provides.', '139435173', 'applestore', 'Mexico', 'Very good', 'It is very good app, in fact I prefer to use it before google maps, although it would be well to optimize the battery consumption since you get off fast and as for the maps, perhaps it is more convenient to have more street names in order to be able to visualize them better, or Put more points of reference of establishments so that it works better the search of places in the map.', 'Waze', 0.230647, 0, 0, 0, 1, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'long', 505, 0, 2, 0.75, 'ot', 'ot'),
